# Multiplayer VFX Sync — Hard Gate

Every visual effect MUST be seen by ALL online players, not just the player who triggers it. This applies to:

- Skill animations and particles (`triggerSkillAnimation`)
- Level-up effects (`spawnLevelUpEffect`)
- Buff/debuff activation particles
- Sprite effects (spriteEffectSystem.spawn)
- Screen shake/flash from shared events (e.g., dragon roar)
- Floor transition effects
- Hit marks, damage numbers from remote combat
- Any new particle, sprite, or overlay effect

## Required Workflow

Before writing or reviewing any VFX-related code:

1. Read the skill `.cursor/skills/multiplayer-vfx-sync/SKILL.md` for the broadcast/replay pattern.
2. Verify the effect is emitted as a `VfxEvent` so remote clients can replay it.
3. Never fire a visual-only call (particles, sprite effects, screen flash) without also pushing a `VfxEvent` when in multiplayer.

## Quick Check

When you add or touch a visual effect, answer these:

- [ ] Does this effect fire on the originating client? (local playback)
- [ ] Is a `VfxEvent` pushed to `pendingVfxEvents` so other players receive it?
- [ ] Does the receiving client replay the effect at the correct world position?
- [ ] Is the originating client's own event filtered out to avoid double-play?

If any box is unchecked, the feature is incomplete.
